7 Ityraeis] foreign mercenaries. Ityraea was a region on the east of the Jordan opposite Galilee, S. Luke iii. 1. It was overrun by Pompey during his eastern campaign in 6 3, and he probably brought over some of the inhabitants to serve in the Roman army, as they were noted for their skill in archery3 cp. Verg. Georg. 11. 448 Ityraeos taxi torquentur in arcus. Antony served in the same campaign, Plut. Ant. 3, and may have brought some back in his retinue: cp. 5 112 cur homines omnium gentium maxime barbaros, Ityraeos, cum sagittis deducis in sorum?
